Method Detail

getSubscriberStatusForContactId

public int getSubscriberStatusForContactId(long contactId)
Returns the IMS subscriber status for a contact. The contact will be reported as an IMS subscriber, if any of his/her phone numbers has IMS capabilities. If the contact is not found in the database, the state will be reported as unknown.

Refer to:
ImsConstants.STATE_IMS_CONTACT
ImsConstants.STATE_NON_IMS_CONTACT
ImsConstants.STATE_UNKNOWN

Parameters:
contactId - The contact ID, as found in the native address book.
Returns:
The IMS subscriber state of this contact, as defined in ImsConstants.

getSubscriberStatusForRawContactId

public int getSubscriberStatusForRawContactId(long rawContactId)
Returns the IMS subscriber status for a contact. The contact will be reported as an IMS subscriber, if any of his/her phone numbers has IMS capabilities. If the contact is not found in the database, the state will be reported as unknown.

Refer to:
ImsConstants.STATE_IMS_CONTACT
ImsConstants.STATE_NON_IMS_CONTACT
ImsConstants.STATE_UNKNOWN

Parameters:
rawContactId - The raw contact ID (as found in the native address book).
Returns:
The IMS subscriber state of this contact, as defined in ImsConstants.

getSubscriberStatus

public int getSubscriberStatus(java.lang.String userId)
Returns the IMS subscriber status for a user ID. If the user ID is not found in the database, the state will be reported as unknown.

Refer to:
ImsConstants.STATE_IMS_CONTACT
ImsConstants.STATE_NON_IMS_CONTACT
ImsConstants.STATE_UNKNOWN

Parameters:
userId - The user ID (in IMS, this is usually an MSISDN).
Returns:
The IMS subscriber state of this user ID, as defined in ImsConstants.

getUserIdsForContactId

public java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getUserIdsForContactId(long contactId)
Retrieves all user IDs for a given contact ID. In IMS, a user ID is usually a phone number.

Parameters:
contactId - The contact ID of the contact, as found in the native address book.
Returns:
A set containing all of the user IDs that belong to this contact. This set will be empty if the contact ID is unknown.

getUserIdsForRawContactId

public java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getUserIdsForRawContactId(long rawContactId)
Retrieves all user IDs for a given raw contact ID. In IMS, a user ID is usually a phone number.

Parameters:
rawContactId - The raw contact ID of the contact, as found in the native address book.
Returns:
A set containing all of the user IDs that belong to this contact. This set will be empty if the raw contact ID is unknown.

getImsContactIds

public java.util.Set<java.lang.Long> getImsContactIds()
Retrieves a Set, containing the contact IDs of all known IMS contacts.

Returns:
A Set containing the contact IDs of all known IMS contacts. The set will be empty if there are no known IMS contacts.

getContactId

public long getContactId(java.lang.String userId)
Retrieves the contact ID for a given user ID. In IMS a user ID is usually a phone number. If this number has stored for multiple contacts in the native address book, only the first occurrence will be returned.

Parameters:
userId - The user ID to look up.
Returns:
The contact ID of the contact with this user ID (or -1 if there is no such contact).

getRawContactId

public long getRawContactId(java.lang.String userId)
Retrieves the raw contact ID for a given user ID. In IMS a user ID is usually a phone number. If this number has stored for multiple contacts in the native address book, only the first occurrence will be returned.

Parameters:
userId - The user ID to look up
Returns:
The raw contact ID of the contact with this user ID (or -1 if there is none).

containsUserId

public boolean containsUserId(java.lang.String userId)
Checks whether a given user ID belongs to a known contact (within the native address book). In IMS, a user ID is usually a phone number.

Parameters:
userId - The user ID to look up.
Returns:
True, if the user ID belongs to a contact in the address book, false otherwise.
